    "movements": [
      {
        "turn": 1,
        "name": "Act 1",
        "intent": "[The hearing room gathers itself under a hard, salt-stained light; papers lie squared, chairs scrape, and every face turns toward the empty place where an answer ought to stand. Outside, the weather presses at the windows without yet giving up its story.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 5,
        "name": "Act 2",
        "intent": "[The hearing room exhales around the bearing-book, its number seeming colder than any accusation spoken before it. The papers are gathered into a neater stack, and the next silence comes shuttered and narrow, as though the room must now look at what its certainty has left unlit.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 10,
        "name": "Act 3",
        "intent": "[The room changes temperature without any window opening, the old accusation gone and a worse emptiness left in its place. A fresh bundle is brought to the clerk's elbow, tied in stained tape, and the next act begins with the smell of closed places about to be opened.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 17,
        "name": "Act 4",
        "intent": "[The locked book is closed, and its clasp sounds too small for the silence that follows. The room shifts from papers to thresholds: rain taps the panes, the door stands watched, and the next act begins with the pressure of the outside night coming in.]"
      }
    ],
    "tutorNotes": []
  },
